They last received their salary more than three months ago. A strike leader said they had been refused the right to sign contracts despite the risks associated with the disease, and if infected, a doctor or nurse was just sacked. Most of the DRC 7,500 registered infections are in the capital. In May, the prime minister said more than $10m had been allocated to fighting coronavirus, but the man in charge says he has received less than $1.5m.
--BBC-